{"title_page": "W. S. Merwin bibliography", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia bibliography}}\n'''William Stanley Merwin''' (September 30, 1927 \u2013 March 15, 2019) was an American poet, credited with over fifty books of poetry, translation and [[prose]].<ref name=Authorship>{{cite web |title=Amazon.com Official Profile |url=https://www.amazon.com/W.-S.-Merwin/e/B000APD3S6/ref=ntt_dp_epwbk_0 |accessdate=7 October 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Poetry==\n;Collections\n* [[1952 in poetry|1952]]: ''A Mask for Janus'', New Haven, Connecticut: [[Yale University Press]]; awarded the [[Yale Series of Younger Poets Competition|Yale Younger Poets Prize]], 1952 (reprinted as part of ''The First Four Books of Poems'', 1975)<ref name=pfwsm>[http://www.poetryfoundation.org/archive/poet.html?id=4676 Merwin biography] at Poetry Foundation, Accessed October 23, 2010</ref>\n* [[1954 in poetry|1954]]: ''The Dancing Bears'', New Haven, Connecticut: Yale University Press (reprinted as part of ''The First Four Books of Poems'', 1975)<ref name=pfwsm/>\n* [[1956 in poetry|1956]]: ''Green with Beasts'', New York: Knopf (reprinted as part of ''The First Four Books of Poems'', 1975)<ref name=pfwsm/>\n* [[1960 in poetry|1960]]: ''The Drunk in the Furnace'', New York: Macmillan (reprinted as part of ''The First Four Books of Poems'', 1975)<ref name=pfwsm/>\n* [[1963 in poetry|1963]]: ''The Moving Target'', New York: Atheneum<ref name=pfwsm/>\n* [[1966 in poetry|1966]]: ''Collected Poems'', New York: Atheneum<ref name=pfwsm/>\n* [[1967 in poetry|1967]]: ''The Lice'', New York: Atheneum; (reprinted in 2017, Port Townsend, Washington: [[Copper Canyon Press]])\n* [[1969 in poetry|1969]]: ''Animae'', San Francisco: Kayak<ref name=pfwsm/>\n* [[1970 in poetry|1970]]: ''The Carrier of Ladders'', New York: Atheneum<ref name=pfwsm/> \u2013 winner of the Pulitzer Prize<ref name=pulitzer>[http://www.pulitzer.org/bycat/Poetry \"Poetry\"]. ''Past winners & finalists by category''. The Pulitzer Prizes. Retrieved 2012-04-08.</ref>\n* [[1970 in poetry|1970]]: ''Signs'', illustrated by [[A. D. Moore]]; Iowa City, Iowa: Stone Wall Press<ref name=pfwsm/>\n* [[1973 in poetry|1973]]: ''Writings to an Unfinished Accompaniment'', New York: Atheneum<ref name=pfwsm/>\n* [[1975 in poetry|1975]]: ''The First Four Books of Poems'', containing ''A Mask for Janus'', ''The Dancing Bears'', ''Green with Beasts'', and ''The Drunk in the Furnace'', New York: Atheneum; (reprinted in 2000, Port Townsend, Washington: [[Copper Canyon Press]])<ref name=pfwsm/>\n* [[1977 in poetry|1977]]: ''The Compass Flower'', New York: Atheneum<ref name=pfwsm/>\n* [[1978 in poetry|1978]]: ''Feathers From the Hill'', Iowa City, Iowa: Windhover<ref name=pfwsm/>\n* [[1982 in poetry|1982]]: ''Finding the Islands'', San Francisco: North Point Press<ref name=pfwsm/>\n* [[1983 in poetry|1983]]: ''Opening the Hand'', New York: Atheneum<ref name=pfwsm/>\n* [[1988 in poetry|1988]]: ''The Rain in the Trees'', New York: Knopf<ref name=pfwsm/>\n* [[1988 in poetry|1988]]: ''Selected Poems'', New York: Atheneum<ref name=pfwsm/>\n* [[1993 in poetry|1993]]: ''The Second Four Books of Poems'', Port Townsend, Washington: Copper Canyon Press\n* [[1993 in poetry|1993]]: ''Travels: Poems'', New York: Knopf<ref name=pfwsm/> \u2013 winner of the 1993 [[Lenore Marshall Poetry Prize]]<ref name=locpws>News release, [https://www.loc.gov/today/pr/1997/97-155.html \"Poet W.S. Merwin Reads at Library of Congress October 15], September 22, 1997, Library of Congress website, retrieved June 8, 2010</ref>\n* [[1996 in poetry|1996]]: ''The Vixen: Poems'', New York: Knopf<ref name=pfwsm/>\n* [[1997 in poetry|1997]]: ''Flower and Hand: Poems, 1977\u20131983'' Port Townsend, Washington: Copper Canyon Press<ref name=pfwsm/>\n* [[1998 in poetry|1998]]: ''The Folding Cliffs: A Narrative'', a \"novel-in-verse\" New York: Knopf<ref>[https://www.amazon.com/Folding-Cliffs-Narrative-W-S-Merwin/dp/0375401482 \"The Folding Cliffs: A Narrative (Hardcover)\"]; [[Amazon.com]]; 2010</ref>\n* [[1999 in poetry|1999]]: ''The River Sound: Poems'', New York: Knopf<ref name=pfwsm/>\n* [[2001 in poetry|2001]]: ''The Pupil'', New York: Knopf<ref name=pfwsm/>\n* [[2005 in poetry|2005]]: ''Migration: New and Selected Poems'', Port Townsend, Washington: Copper Canyon Press<ref name=pfwsm/> \u2013 winner of the [[National Book Award for Poetry]]<ref name=nba2005>\n[https://www.nationalbook.org/awards-prizes/national-book-awards-2005 \"National Book Awards \u2013 2005\"]. [[National Book Foundation]]. Retrieved 2012-04-08. <br/>(With acceptance speech by Merwin, essay by Patrick Rosal from the Awards 60-year anniversary blog, and other material.)</ref>\n* [[2005 in poetry|2005]]: ''Present Company'', Port Townsend, Washington: Copper Canyon Press<ref name=pfwsm/>\n* [[2007 in poetry|2005]]:  ''Selected Poems'', Tarset, Northumberland, UK: [[Bloodaxe Books]]\n*[[2008 in poetry|2008]]: ''The Shadow of Sirius'', Port Townsend, Washington: [[Copper Canyon Press]]<ref>Farr, Sheila,  [http://seattletimes.nwsource.com/html/books/2008327531_br02merwin.html \"Poet ponders life's contrasts in 'The Shadow of Sirius'\"], book review, October 30, 2010, ''The Seattle Times'', retrieved June 8, 2010</ref> \u2013 winner of the Pulitzer Prize;<ref name=\"pulitzer\" /> 2009: Tarset, Northumberland, UK: [[Bloodaxe Books]]\n* [[2013 in poetry|2013]]: ''The Collected Poems of W. S. Merwin'', New York: [[Library of America]]\n* [[2014 in poetry|2014]]: ''The Moon Before Morning'', Port Townsend, Washington: [[Copper Canyon Press]];<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.coppercanyonpress.org/memorial/|title=W.S. Merwin|website=www.coppercanyonpress.org}}</ref> Hexham, Northumberland, UK: [[Bloodaxe Books]]\n* [[2016 in poetry|2016]]: ''Garden Time'', Port Townsend, Washington: [[Copper Canyon Press]];<ref name=\"web.archive.org\">{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180121071946/https://www.coppercanyonpress.org/pages/browse/book.asp?bg=370D5539-31F0-4B38-89AF-D57D1E0ACE25|title=Copper Canyon Press: Garden Time, poetry by W.S. Merwin|date=January 21, 2018|website=web.archive.org}}</ref> Hexham, Northumberland, UK: [[Bloodaxe Books]]\n* [[2017 in poetry|2017]]: ''The Essential W.S. Merwin'', Port Townsend, Washington: [[Copper Canyon Press]]<ref name=\"coppercanyonpress.org\">{{cite web|url=https://www.coppercanyonpress.org/pages/browse/book.asp?bg=%7B5BF5192A-E36A-4DF9-8BF9-18155B7EA04C%7D|title=Copper Canyon Press: The Essential W.S. Merwin, Poetry by W.S. Merwin|website=Coppercanyonpress.org|accessdate=21 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n;List of poems\n{|class='wikitable sortable' width='90%'\n|-\n!width=25%|Title\n!|Year\n!|First published\n!|Reprinted/collected\n|-\n|[http://www.newyorker.com/fiction/poetry/2008/11/03/081103po_poem_merwin Alba]\n|2008\n|[[The New Yorker]] 84/35 (November 3, 2008)\n| \n|-\n|[http://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2014/10/20/blackboard The Blackboard]\n|2014\n|[[The New Yorker]] 90/32 (October 20, 2014)\n| \n|-\n|Shadow Questions\n|2016\n|Garden Time (2016)\n|-\n|Another Year Comes\n|1960\n|\n|The New Yorker Book of Poems (1974)\n|-\n|The Asians Dying \n|1966\n|\n|The New Yorker Book of Poems (1974)\n|-\n|Burning Mountain\n|1958\n|\n|-\n|Forgetting clouds\n|[[2014 in poetry|2014]]\n|{{cite journal <!--|author= |authormask=1 -->|date=April 21, 2014 |title=Forgetting clouds |department= |journal=The New Yorker |volume=90 |issue=9 |pages=56 |url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2014/04/21/forgetting-clouds |<!--accessdate=2018-11-26-->}}\n|\n|-\n|The Herds\n|1966\n|\n|The New Yorker Book of Poems (1974)\n|-\n|Lemuels Blessing\n|1962\n|\n|The New Yorker Book of Poems (1974)\n|-\n|The Old Room\n|1969\n|\n|The New Yorker Book of Poems (1974)\n|-\n|Peasant\n|1967\n|\n|The New Yorker Book of Poems (1974)\n|-\n|Plea for a Captive\n|1960\n|\n|The New Yorker Book of Poems (1974)\n|-\n|The Portland (Going Out)\n|1957\n|\n|The New Yorker Book of Poems (1974)\n|-\n|Resolution \n|1964\n|\n