  = 25\n| nationalgoals1      = 9\n| manageryears1       = 2015\n| managerclubs1       = [[Turkey national under-17 football team|Turkey U17]] (coach)\n| manageryears2       = 2015\n| managerclubs2       = [[Kayseri Erciyesspor]]\n| manageryears3       = 2016\n| managerclubs3       = [[Boluspor]]\n| manageryears4       = 2017\u20132018\n| managerclubs4       = [[Manisaspor]]\n| manageryears5       = 2018\n| managerclubs5       = [[Denizlispor]]\n| manageryears6       = 2018\u20132019\n| managerclubs6       = [[\u0130stanbulspor]]\n| manageryears7       = 2020\u2013\n| managerclubs7       = [[\u0130stanbulspor]]\n| medaltemplates      =\n| club-update         = \n| nationalteam-update = \n}}\n\n'''Fatih Tekke''' (born 9 September 1977), known by his ''given nickname'' '''[[Sultan]]''',<ref name=\"Nickname (1)\">{{cite news|first=|last=|authorlink=|author=|coauthors=|curly=|title=Fatih Sultan Tekke|url=https://www.fanatik.com.tr/fatih-sultan-tekke-224649|format=|agency=|work=|publisher=[[Fanatik]]|location=|id=|pages=|page=|date=13 May 2011|access-date=4 August 2019|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20190804133119/https://www.fanatik.com.tr/fatih-sultan-tekke-224649|archive-date=4 August 2019|quote=|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Nickname (2)\">{{cite news|first=|last=|authorlink=|author=Elif Sudagezer|coauthors=|curly=|title=Rusya'n\u0131n \u2018Fatih Sultan Tekke'si: FIFA 2018 i\u00e7in Rusya'dan davet bekliyorum|url=https://tr.sputniknews.com/viewpoint-worldcup-2018/201712151031414652-rusya-fifa-dunya-kupas-turk-futbolcu-fatih-tekke-manisaspor-teknik-direktoru-zenit-oyuncu-futbol-sputnik-roportaj/|format=|agency=|work=|publisher=[[Sputnik (news agency)]]|location=|id=|pages=|page=|date=15 December 2017|access-date=4 August 2019|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20190804133202/https://tr.sputniknews.com/viewpoint-worldcup-2018/201712151031414652-rusya-fifa-dunya-kupas-turk-futbolcu-fatih-tekke-manisaspor-teknik-direktoru-zenit-oyuncu-futbol-sputnik-roportaj/|archive-date=4 August 2019|quote=|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"Nickname (3)\">{{cite news|first=|last=|authorlink=|author=Emir Kolayl\u0131|coauthors=|curly=|title=Fatih Sultan Tekke|url=https://fourfourtwo.com.tr/fatih-sultan-tekke/|format=|agency=|work=|publisher=[[FourFourTwo|FourFourTwo Turkish Edition]]|location=|id=|pages=|page=|date=25 December 2013|access-date=4 August 2019|language=Tr|archive-url=https://archive.today/20190804133330/https://fourfourtwo.com.tr/fatih-sultan-tekke/|archive-date=4 August 2019|quote=|url-status=live}}</ref> is a [[Turkey|Turkish]] [[Association football|football]] coach and former player who is currently the manager of [[\u0130stanbulspor]].\n\n==Club career==\n===Turkey===\nTekke was born in the small town of [[K\u00f6pr\u00fcba\u015f\u0131, Trabzon|K\u00f6pr\u00fcba\u015f\u0131]], in the province of [[Trabzon Province|Trabzon]]. He joined [[Trabzonspor]], the major team in the area. Tekke was still in his teens when he started to appear in the first team. In 45 matches that he played between 1994\u20131997, he scored 6 goals. At the beginning of the 1997\u20131998 season he was loaned out to [[Altay SK]] of [[\u0130zmir]], where he scored 8 goals in 24 matches. In a 4\u20135 defeat to [[Galatasaray S.K. (football team)|Galatasaray]], he scored a hat-trick. However a few weeks later he broke his leg and was out of the game for six months. Upon his return to Trabzonspor, Tekke played another 38 matches and scored 6 goals before he transferred to [[Gaziantepspor]] in the summer of 2000. In this period he made his first appearance for the [[Turkish national football team|Turkish national team]].\n\nIn 2002, Tekke returned to Trabzonspor and was given the captaincy. This was the time Tekke reached the peak of his career. In the 2004\u201305 season he managed to become the league's top goal scorer with 31 goals, 7 goals ahead of the second placed player and was second for the [[Golden Foot]]. During his spell with Trabzonspor, he won two medals for winning the [[Turkish Cup]] in consecutive seasons.\n\n===Russia===\nIn July 2006, he signed for [[FC Zenit St. Petersburg|Zenit St. Petersburg]]. On 6 August 2006, Tekke scored on his debut for the club, as he came off the bench against [[FC Shinnik Yaroslavl|Shinnik Yaroslavl]] and scored the only goal of the game for his team to win 1\u20130. Tekke scored the winning goal in the [[UEFA Cup]] group stage in a 3\u20132 victory over [[Athlitiki Enosi Larissa F.C.|AE Larissa]]. He assisted the second in the [[2008 UEFA Cup Final]] win over [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]. On 21 October 2008, Tekke scored in the 1\u20131 draw with [[FC BATE Borisov|BATE Borisov]] in the Champions League. On 3 February 2010, Tekke signed a 3-year contract with [[FC Rubin Kazan]]. He only played five games before he decided to return to Turkey, transferring to [[Be\u015fikta\u015f]].\n\n===Back to Turkey===\nOn 1 September 2010, Tekke signed a 2-year contract with [[Besiktas JK]]. However, he was only able to play a total of two games before he was sent to [[Ankarag\u00fcc\u00fc]], in the 2010\u20132011 transfer window. In the five matches he played for Ankarag\u00fcc\u00fc, he scored three goals. In the summer transfer season of 2011, the newly promoted team, [[Orduspor]], declared that they had purchased Tekke from [[Ankarag\u00fcc\u00fc]]. Tekke was given the number 23 and the captaincy of the team. He then moved to [[Orduspor]] and retired soon after. He then became a manager.\n\n==International career==\nTekke was in the Turkish national squad for U15, U16, U17, U18, U21, and for the [[Turkish national football team|Turkish national team]]. For U15, he played 6 matches and scored no goals. For U16, he played 18 matches and scored 5 goals, while also winning the [[1994 UEFA European Under-16 Football Championship|UEFA European Under-16 Championship]], held in Ireland. For U17, he played 10 matches and scored no goals. For U18, he played 13 matches and scored 5 goals. For U21, he only played 1 match. Finally between 1998\u20132007, Tekke played 32 matches and scored 9 goals for the [[Turkish national football team|Turkish national team]].\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|10 November 2009}}<ref>{{NFT player|id=6790|name=Tekke, Fatih| accessdate=15 September 2010 }}</ref>\n\n===Club===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Europe\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\"|[[Trabzonspor]]\n|[[Turkish First Football League 1994\u201395|1994\u201395]]\n|4||0||2||0||-||-||-||-||6||0\n|-\n|[[Turkish First Football League 1995\u201396|1995\u201396]]\n|20||3||2||1||-||-||-||-||22||4\n|-\n|[[Turkish First Football League 1996\u201397|1996\u201397]]\n|19||3||3||1||-||-||-||-||22||4\n|-\n|[[Turkish First Football League 1997\u201398|1997\u201398]]\n|2||0||-||-||-||-||-||-||2||0\n|-\n!Total\n!45!!6!!7!!2!!0!!0!!0!!0!!52!!8\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Altay S.K.|Altay]]\n|[[Turkish First Football League 1997\u201398|1997\u201398]]\n|24||8||2||1||-||-||-||-||26||9\n|-\n!Total\n!24!!8!!2!!1!!0!!0!!0!!0!!26!!9\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"|[[Trabzonspor]]\n|[[Turkish First Football League 1998\u201399|1998\u201399]]\n|16||4||-||-||-||-||-||-||16||4\n|-\n|[[Turkish First Football League 1999\u20132000|1999\u201300]]\n|22||2||3||0||-||-||-||-||25||2\n|-\n!Total\n!38!!6!!3!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!41!!6\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"|[[Gaziantepspor]]\n|[[Turkish First Football League 2000\u201301|2000\u201301]]\n|31||15||2||0||-||-||-||-||33||15\n|-\n|[[S\u00fcper Lig 2001\u201302|2001\u201302]]\n|24||12||3||2||-||-||-||-||27||14\n|-\n|[[S\u00fcper Lig 2002\u201303|2002\u201303]]\n|2||1||-||-||-||-||-||-||2||1\n|-\n!Total\n!57!!28!!5!!2!!0!!0!!0!!0!!62!!30\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\"|[[Trabzonspor]]\n|[[S\u00fcper Lig 2002\u201303|2002\u201303]]\n